<span id="freeTextContainer8711766379960354915">This was the first book I ever cried over, and it still has quite a bit of emotional power for me!<br/><br/>There&apos;s so much goodness crammed into one book--Halt being a complete grump, people getting thrown into moats, the word &quot;brouhaha&quot; (if you know, you know), Horace being Horace, and GILAN. Also, Evanlyn, and Will being his lovable self. (I honestly feel like Will is a cousin of mine, I&apos;ve read and reread these books so many times.) <br/><br/>And the ending! The freaking cliffhanger ending!! It. Still. Gets. Me</span>
  <span id="freeText8711766379960354915" style="display:none">This was the first book I ever cried over, and it still has quite a bit of emotional power for me!<br /><br />There's so much goodness crammed into one book--Halt being a complete grump, people getting thrown into moats, the word "brouhaha" (if you know, you know), Horace being Horace, and GILAN. Also, Evanlyn, and Will being his lovable self. (I honestly feel like Will is a cousin of mine, I've read and reread these books so many times.) <br /><br />And the ending! The freaking cliffhanger ending!! It. Still. Gets. Me. Every time, I hope it'll end differently...and it doesn't. <br /><br />4.5 stars, rounded up to 5 for GR!</span>
